   January 30, 2002         DOL > Office of Small Business Programs

   Office of Small Business Programs

   The Office of Small Business Programs (OSBP) administers four programs:
    1. Procurement  related utilization of small, small minority, and
       small women-owned businesses, and minority colleges and
       universities, by the Department of Labor.
    2. Department of Labor interaction with and support of Minority
       Colleges and Universities.
    3. Department of Labor's central point for Compliance Assistance
       Information and referral services for small entities.
    4. Administrative oversight of Department Advisory Committees and
       similar activities.


